CABLE theft has crippled Mzansi’s railways for a while now. In an effort to end the continuing cable theft, an operation was led by Major General Max Masha and other law enforcement agencies. Today, an intelligence driven operation involving involving Prasa, City of Joburg and law enforcement, witnessed copper worth about R15 million being seized. Speaking to Daily Sun, Gauteng provincial cops spokesman Captain Kay Makhubele said the operation is still continuing and arrests have been made. “As the country continues to observe lockdown level 1 the operation is also in full swing led by police. We have arrested 20 suspects during this operation and police are still following information about the main culprit of the copper seized in Kliptown,” he said. Makhubele said they are hopeful more arrests will be made today as the operation continues.